quran[27]{c,v,t,f}:
  37,127,"But they rejected him, so they will surely be brought [for punishment],",""
  37,128,"except the chosen slaves of Allah.",""
  37,129,"And We left for him [a favorable mention] among later generations:",""
  37,130,"“Peace be upon Elias.”",""
  37,131,"This is how We reward those who do good.",""
  37,132,"He was one of Our believing slaves.",""
  37,133,"Lot was indeed one of the messengers.",""
  37,134,"When We saved him and all of his household,",""
  37,135,"except an old woman<sup>29</sup> who was among those who stayed behind.","[29] Lot’s wife, who was not a believer."
  37,136,"Then We destroyed the rest.",""
  37,137,"You [Makkans] pass by their ruins by day",""
  37,138,"and by night. Do you still not understand?",""
  37,139,"Jonah was indeed one of the messengers.",""
  37,140,"When he fled to the fully laden ship,",""
  37,141,"then he cast lots<sup>30</sup> with them, but was among those who lost.","[30] To determine who would be cast overboard in order to save the rest of the passengers; the ship was about to sink, for it was overloaded."
  37,142,"The whale then swallowed him while he was blameworthy<sup>31</sup>.","[31] For leaving his people without Allah’s permission."
  37,143,"Were it not for the fact that he was one of those who glorify Allah,",""
  37,144,"he would have stayed in its belly until the Day of Resurrection<sup>32</sup>.","[32] The belly of the fish would have turned to be his grave."
  37,145,"But We cast him ashore on a barren land while he was ill,",""
  37,146,"and caused a gourd vine<sup>33</sup> to grow over him.","[33] For its cooling shade and as food for him."
  37,147,"We sent him<sup>34</sup> to one hundred thousand people or more,","[34] i.e., We sent him thereafter to his people."
  37,148,"and they believed, so We let them enjoy for a while.",""
  37,149,"So ask them, “Does your Lord have daughters while they have sons?”<sup>35</sup>","[35] The pagans of Makkah claimed that angels were Allah’s daughters, while preferring sons for themselves."
  37,150,"Or did We create the angels as females while they were watching?",""
  37,151,"No indeed, it is one of their fabrications when they say,",""
  37,152,"“Allah has children,” and they are truly liars.",""
  37,153,"Did He choose daughters over sons<sup>36</sup>?","[36] i.e., daughters that you hate over sons that you like?"
